SIMPLE: monochromatic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monochromatic
<hw>Mon`o*chro*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>monochromatique</ets>. See <er>Monochrome</er>.]</ety>
<def>Consisting of one color, or presenting rays of light of one color
only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Monochromatic lamp</b></col> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>,<cd>a lamp
whose flame yields rays of some one homogenous light. It is of great
importance in optical experiments.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monochrome</ent>⟦br⟧
